    "body": "Using the context manager is OK, but I wouldn't want to encourage setting this option globally.\n\nI'll typically use `s[np.isfinite(s)]` when I have infinities (which is often). This also doesn't make it clear that you're excluding NaNs (which apparently are defined to not be finite).\n\n+0.5 on adding `dropinf` a method.\n"
