    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The nice thing about `dropna` is you get the `how=any/all` and `axis=0/1` behavior too. If we go the doc route we should include examples on a DataFrame with those. And yeah, `np.isfinite`'s docstring states quite clearly that `NaN` is not finite.\n"
